      • addHitEffects

        public void addHitEffects(net.minecraft.world.World worldObj,
                          net.minecraft.util.math.RayTraceResult target,
                          net.minecraft.client.particle.ParticleManager manager)
        Spawn a digging particle effect in the world, this is a wrapper around EffectRenderer.addBlockHitEffects to allow the multipart more control over the particles. Useful when you have entirely different texture sheets for different sides/locations in the world.
        Parameters:
        worldObj - The current world
        target - The target the player is looking at {x/y/z/side/sub}
        manager - A reference to the current particle manager.

      • addDestroyEffects

        public void addDestroyEffects(net.minecraft.world.World world,
                              net.minecraft.util.math.BlockPos pos,
                              net.minecraft.client.particle.ParticleManager manager)
        Spawn particles for when the multipart is destroyed. Due to the nature of how this is invoked, the x/y/z locations are not always guaranteed to host your block. So be sure to do proper sanity checks before assuming that the location is this block.
        Parameters:
        world - The current world
        pos - Position to spawn the particle
        manager - A reference to the current particle manager.

      • isReplaceable

      • canConnectRedstone

        public boolean canConnectRedstone(net.minecraft.util.EnumFacing side)
        Determine if this block can make a redstone connection on the side provided, Useful to control which sides are inputs and outputs for redstone wires.
        Parameters:
        side - The side that is trying to make the connection, CAN BE NULL
        Returns:
        True to make the connection
